Depending on the envrionment, log information may vary a little bit.

Example of the caller profile to be recorded as follows

[Using SpringRemote]

    [0001][14:14:51 264][    0][    0] EXTERNAL-CALL [RMI] com.sun.proxy.$Proxy1.invoke(Lorg/springframework/remoting/support/RemoteInvocation;)Ljava/lang/Object; [3,966 ms]
    
[Using Java API only]

    [0001][14:17:43 194][    0][    0] EXTERNAL-CALL [RMI] com.sun.proxy.$Proxy0.getMyString()Ljava/lang/String; [4,083 ms]

[Reference]
For RMI call toplogy connection, agent must be installed on both sides and this option must be set to true.

---

* Default : false
* Type : Boolean
* Restart : Required
* Related Options
    * [enable_guid_from_rmi](./agentHelp?key=enable_guid_from_rmi&type=1)
* Supported Version : 5.0.12